  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL-3 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 3. Twelve of thirteen factors are assessed and meet required levels; one factor (Use error) is recorded as not-assessed on the grounds that user-induced variation is considered irrelevant to an automated CFD workflow — a rationale that does not satisfy the not-applicable encoding and leaves a material credibility gap at MRL 3.",
