      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must hold ISO 9001 certification or equivalent documented QA process covering version control, regression testing, and release validation.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1 is deployed under a documented QA plan that includes version-controlled source, automated regression suite (>2000 cases), and formal release validation. ISO 9001 certificate on file. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code must pass at least one published benchmark with documented order-of-accuracy confirmation for the governing equation set used in the hemolysis simulation.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against the Taylor-Green vortex and lid-driven cavity benchmarks with second-order spatial convergence confirmed. Published verification reports accompany the solver release. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for the primary QoI (shear-stress scalar) and must be less than 5% on the fine grid.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the FDA pump geometry (coarse 2.1 M, medium 5.8 M, fine 14.2 M cells). GCI for volume-averaged shear stress: 3.1% (medium-to-fine). Richardson extrapolation applied. Exceeds Gradation 2 requirement; Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, temperature) must be documented with measurement uncertainty and must match simulated boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experiments conducted at 2500 and 3500 RPM, flow rates 2.5–7.5 L/min, 37 °C glycerol-water analogue (viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s ±2%). All boundary conditions replicated in CFD to within measurement uncertainty bands. Test condition fidelity confirmed at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., RMSE or E_rms) between predicted and measured velocity or shear-stress profiles must be reported with uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "PIV velocity comparisons across three axial planes yield E_rms < 8% of bulk velocity for all five operating points. Shear-stress scalar field RMSE = 6.4 Pa against PIV-derived estimates. Comparison is quantitative and within acceptance band. Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (velocity, shear stress) must be demonstrably linked to the COU QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) via a documented hemolysis power-law model.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model maps shear stress and exposure time to hemolysis index. Sensitivity analysis confirms RH is monotonically sensitive to volume-averaged shear stress. QoI relevance chain is documented. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry and operating envelope must overlap with the COU device geometry and the five target flow-speed combinations.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry used in the COU. All five COU operating points (2.5, 4.0, 5.5, 6.5, 7.5 L/min at 2500 and 3500 RPM) fall within the validated envelope. Relevance confirmed at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated by residual reduction of at least four orders of magnitude and by monitoring QoI stability over the final 500 iterations.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residuals below 1×10⁻⁶ for continuity and momentum. RH monitor showed variation < 0.1% over final 500 iterations across all five operating points. Solver error contribution is negligible. Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Analyst-induced variation in model setup (boundary condition selection, turbulence model choice, meshing decisions) should be characterised through inter-analyst or sensitivity studies.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that use error is not a relevant consideration for this COU because the CFD workflow is fully scripted and executed through an automated pipeline with no manual analyst intervention at run time. Accordingly, no inter-analyst study or sensitivity analysis for setup choices was conducted. The factor is therefore left without a formal assessment. Note: this rationale describes a condition that would ordinarily be encoded as 'not-applicable'; however, the automated-pipeline argument has not been independently verified, and the factor has not been formally scoped out under the ASME V&V 40 Table 5-1 process."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The turbulence closure and hemolysis sub-model must be justified against published literature for rotating blood-contacting devices, and sensitivity to turbulence model choice must be reported.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on prior FDA pump round-robin studies showing best agreement with PIV data. Comparison against realizable k-ε and RSM performed; SST k-ω yields lowest E_rms. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model is the regulatory standard for relative comparisons. Model form uncertainty documented. Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (blood viscosity, density) and geometric inputs (impeller dimensions) must be sourced from traceable measurements with stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Blood analogue viscosity measured at 37 °C using calibrated rheometer (±1.5%). Pump geometry digitised from CMM measurements of production impeller (±0.02 mm). All inputs traceable to primary standards. Input uncertainty propagated via ±5% viscosity perturbation study; RH sensitivity < 3%. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples (pump units used in validation testing) must be from the same production lot or dimensionally verified to be within manufacturing tolerances of the COU device.",
      "rationale": "Three pump units from the same production batch used in PIV experiments. CMM inspection confirms all critical dimensions within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Sample representativeness documented in test report TR-2024-CPB-001. Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Non-dimensional equivalency (Reynolds number, flow coefficient) between validation experiments and COU operating conditions must be demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "Reynolds numbers for all five COU operating points (Re = 4 200–11 800) fall within the validated range (Re = 3 800–12 500). Flow coefficients φ match to within 4%. Non-dimensional equivalency confirmed via tabulated comparison in assessment report section 6.3. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    }
